      "value": "<h2></b>Description</b></h2></p><p>This altar is a deceptively complex, many-chambered scroll rack or bookshelf capable of securing dozens of documents. Unlike most altars, its magic circle effects a re a ligned against one o r two alignment components (such as only good or both evil and law) appropriate to the interests of the temple. Praying at the altar grants a +2 circumstance bonus on Knowledge (arcana), Perception, Spellcraft, and Use Magic Device checks; in addition, the worshiper selects one spell or spell-like ability it can cast and treats its caster level as 1 higher than normal when casting that spell.<br><p><b>Base Item:</b> </p><h3><b>Requirements</b></h3><p>Craft Wondrous Item, Heighten Spell, guidance, magic circle  against chaos/evil/good/law (as appropriate), creator must  worship Nethys</p><h3><b>Source: </b></h3>Inner Sea Gods",
